news_header: Georgians are voting in parliamentary elections, with the Georgian Dream Party facing challenges in maintaining power.
news_text: The leader of the Georgian Dream Party, which has been in power for 12 years, is facing parliamentary elections where support is predicted to be below 40%. The party may struggle to form a government independently, leading to potential collaboration with the European Opposition. Georgia became an EU candidate in December, but its membership process has stalled due to political developments since last summer.
